-------------
WORD SEARCH
-------------
	
The following program is used to search through text files in to see if they contain a word specified by the user. Once run the program will output the names of any file that did contain the word.
	
-----------
How To Run
-----------

To run the program simply execute the shell script. Followed by the word you wish to search for and the files you wish to search through.

e.g

./run.sh example file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt

The above will search through files file1.txt, file2.txt & file3.txt for an instance of the string "example".

Example out put could be:

/run.sh hello file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt
file1.txt
file3.txt

which would indicate the word "hello" was found in file1.txt & file3.txt



